name: r-ggextra
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "0.10.0" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-ggextra
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  fn: ggExtra_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/ggExtra_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/ggExtra/ggExtra_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: dc6855bbb7e81ffa58d6b65b594d22718fa36b7f50b2284386f70fa8ccc6a3e5

build:
  noarch: generic
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 0
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-colourpicker >=1.0
    - r-ggplot2 >=2.2.0
    - r-gtable >=0.2.0
    - r-miniui >=0.1.1
    - r-scales >=0.2.0
    - r-shiny >=0.13.0
    - r-shinyjs >=0.5.2
    - r-r6
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-colourpicker >=1.0
    - r-ggplot2 >=2.2.0
    - r-gtable >=0.2.0
    - r-miniui >=0.1.1
    - r-scales >=0.2.0
    - r-shiny >=0.13.0
    - r-shinyjs >=0.5.2
    - r-r6

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('ggExtra')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('ggExtra')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/daattali/ggExtra
  license: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: Collection of functions and layers to enhance 'ggplot2'. The  flagship function is 'ggMarginal()', which can be used to add marginal histograms/boxplots/density plots to 'ggplot2' scatterplots.
  license_family: MIT

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
